SELECT
  10,
  1,
  3,
  'Which summary best fits the movement of 2 Samuel 1?',
  '["A messenger brings David news of Saul and Jonathan''s death, hoping for reward, but instead he meets grief and judgment. David composes a lament that honors Saul as Israel''s fallen king and Jonathan as his beloved friend. The chapter begins David''s reign with sorrow rather than triumph.", "David orders a census, then recognizes that the counting was sinful and chooses to fall into the LORD''s hand rather than man''s. A plague strikes Israel until David builds an altar on Araunah''s threshing floor and offers sacrifices. The chapter ends with judgment checked by mercy and a site that will later matter deeply in Israel''s worship life.", "David seeks the LORD and goes to Hebron, where Judah anoints him king, while Abner makes Ish-bosheth king over the rest of Israel. The chapter''s conflicts begin with a brutal contest at Gibeon and end with Asahel''s death and Joab''s hard-won victory. It shows a kingdom split before it is unified.", "Abner turns against Ish-bosheth and promises to bring all Israel to David, but Joab kills him in revenge for Asahel''s death. David distances himself from the murder, laments Abner publicly, and refuses to let his own house appear guilty. The chapter strengthens David''s legitimacy while exposing the violence around him."]'::jsonb,
  'A messenger brings David news of Saul and Jonathan''s death, hoping for reward, but instead he meets grief and judgment. David composes a lament that honors Saul as Israel''s fallen king and Jonathan as his beloved friend. The chapter begins David''s reign with sorrow rather than triumph.',
  'This summary captures the movement of 2 Samuel 1 (2 Samuel 1:1-10-2 Samuel 1:11-27).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 10
    AND chapter = 1
    AND difficulty_stage = 3
    AND prompt = 'Which summary best fits the movement of 2 Samuel 1?'
);

