  '["When Ish-bosheth''s captains bring him the news of Abner''s death, two men murder him in his house and flee with his head. David again refuses to reward violence, executing the assassins and honoring the slain king with burial. The chapter removes Saul''s last rival by treachery rather than battle.", "The tribes finally come together and anoint David king over all Israel at Hebron. David captures Jerusalem from the Jebusites, makes it his stronghold, and grows stronger as the LORD establishes him. Philistine attacks follow, but David seeks God''s guidance and wins decisive victories.", "David searches for anyone from Saul''s house to show covenant kindness for Jonathan''s sake and finds Mephibosheth, Jonathan''s crippled son. He restores Saul''s land to him and gives him a permanent place at the king''s table. The chapter turns royal power into mercy and memory.", "After insult to David''s envoys, the Ammonites hire Aramean allies and prepare for war. Joab divides the army, the battle turns when the enemy retreats, and David''s forces follow up with a larger campaign against the Arameans. The chapter shows David''s kingdom defending its honor and gaining strength through coordinated leadership."]'::jsonb,
  'When Ish-bosheth''s captains bring him the news of Abner''s death, two men murder him in his house and flee with his head. David again refuses to reward violence, executing the assassins and honoring the slain king with burial. The chapter removes Saul''s last rival by treachery rather than battle.',
  'This final perspective fits 2 Samuel 4 (2 Samuel 4:1-8-2 Samuel 4:9-12).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
