  '["David brings the ark toward Jerusalem, but Uzzah dies when he touches it, forcing David to slow down and rethink reverence. The ark rests in Obed-edom''s house, then returns with joy as David dances before the LORD while Michal despises him. The chapter balances celebration with the fear of holy things.", "David wants to build a house for the LORD, but the LORD instead promises to build David a lasting house and kingdom. Nathan relays the covenant that will outlast David''s reign and tie his line to future kingship. David responds with humility and awe, recognizing that God has spoken grace beyond his request.", "David defeats the Philistines, Moab, Hadadezer, the Arameans, and the Edomites, securing tribute from many surrounding peoples. He dedicates the spoils to the LORD and appoints officers over his expanding kingdom. The chapter shows a monarch whose victories are disciplined by worship and administration.", "David searches for anyone from Saul''s house to show covenant kindness for Jonathan''s sake and finds Mephibosheth, Jonathan''s crippled son. He restores Saul''s land to him and gives him a permanent place at the king''s table. The chapter turns royal power into mercy and memory."]'::jsonb,
  'David brings the ark toward Jerusalem, but Uzzah dies when he touches it, forcing David to slow down and rethink reverence. The ark rests in Obed-edom''s house, then returns with joy as David dances before the LORD while Michal despises him. The chapter balances celebration with the fear of holy things.',
  'This summary line expresses the narrative function of 2 Samuel 6.'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
