  'While Joab is at war, David stays behind, sees Bathsheba, and commits adultery that leads into deception and murder. Uriah refuses the comforts of home while his comrades fight, and David arranges his death in battle to cover the sin. The chapter is the moral turning point of David''s reign.',
  'This summary captures the movement of 2 Samuel 11 (2 Samuel 11:1-5-2 Samuel 11:1-27).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 10
    AND chapter = 11
    AND difficulty_stage = 3
    AND prompt = 'Which summary best fits the movement of 2 Samuel 11?'
);

