  3,
  'Which summary best fits the movement of 2 Samuel 15?',
  '["Absalom wins hearts in Israel and stages a conspiracy that forces David to flee Jerusalem barefoot and grieving. Loyal servants, priests, and counselors all face hard choices as the king leaves the city. The chapter shows the cost of sin rippling outward into public collapse.", "Joab uses a wise woman from Tekoa to press David to think about bringing back Absalom. David relents, but when Absalom is restored he remains half-healed and unsatisfied, living in Jerusalem yet not seeing the king''s face. The chapter shows reconciliation managed politically rather than spiritually.", "As David escapes, Ziba opportunistically claims Mephibosheth''s loyalty, and Shimei curses David with stones and dust. David refuses revenge and leaves judgment to God while Hushai arrives in Jerusalem to counter Ahithophel''s counsel. The chapter is full of mixed motives, but David keeps moving with restraint.", "Ahithophel gives Absalom a ruthless plan to strike David immediately, but Hushai gives a slower counsel designed to buy David time. The warning is carried through loyal messengers, and when Ahithophel sees his counsel rejected he goes home and hangs himself. The chapter shows wisdom fighting wisdom while God protects David through delay."]'::jsonb,
