  'What final perspective best fits 2 Samuel 24?',
  '["David orders a census, then recognizes that the counting was sinful and chooses to fall into the LORD''s hand rather than man''s. A plague strikes Israel until David builds an altar on Araunah''s threshing floor and offers sacrifices. The chapter ends with judgment checked by mercy and a site that will later matter deeply in Israel''s worship life.", "A messenger brings David news of Saul and Jonathan''s death, hoping for reward, but instead he meets grief and judgment. David composes a lament that honors Saul as Israel''s fallen king and Jonathan as his beloved friend. The chapter begins David''s reign with sorrow rather than triumph.", "The tribes finally come together and anoint David king over all Israel at Hebron. David captures Jerusalem from the Jebusites, makes it his stronghold, and grows stronger as the LORD establishes him. Philistine attacks follow, but David seeks God''s guidance and wins decisive victories.", "David brings the ark toward Jerusalem, but Uzzah dies when he touches it, forcing David to slow down and rethink reverence. The ark rests in Obed-edom''s house, then returns with joy as David dances before the LORD while Michal despises him. The chapter balances celebration with the fear of holy things."]'::jsonb,
  'David orders a census, then recognizes that the counting was sinful and chooses to fall into the LORD''s hand rather than man''s. A plague strikes Israel until David builds an altar on Araunah''s threshing floor and offers sacrifices. The chapter ends with judgment checked by mercy and a site that will later matter deeply in Israel''s worship life.',
  'This final perspective fits 2 Samuel 24 (2 Samuel 24:1-9-2 Samuel 24:1-17).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 10
    AND chapter = 24
    AND difficulty_stage = 5
    AND prompt = 'What final perspective best fits 2 Samuel 24?'
);

